题目：How is the equilibrium constant expressed for high-pressure gas reactions? Is $\prod_B \left( rac{p_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B}$ for high-pressure gas reactions only a function of temperature? Is $\prod_B \left( rac{p_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B}$ the same for the same gas reaction at high and low pressure? Is $\prod_B \left( rac{f_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B}$ at high pressure the same as $\prod_B \left( rac{p_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B}$ at low pressure? Is $\prod_B \left( rac{f_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B}$ at low pressure the same as $\prod_B \left( rac{p_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B}$ at low pressure?
问：Expressions and comparisons for high-pressure gas equilibrium constants

解题过程：
For high-pressure gases, $K^{	heta} = \prod_B \left( rac{p_B}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B} \prod_B \gamma_B^{
u_B}$. $\prod_B \left( rac{p_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B}$ is not only a function of temperature but also pressure, so it differs at high and low pressure. $\prod_B \left( rac{f_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B}$ at high pressure equals $K^{	heta}$, which is the same as $\prod_B \left( rac{p_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B}$ at low pressure (since $\gamma_B \approx 1$). At low pressure, $\prod_B \left( rac{f_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B} \approx \prod_B \left( rac{p_B^{	ext{eq}}}{p^{	heta}}ight)^{
u_B}$.

最终答案：['A']

